(55, 1, '2016-06-13 15:48:45', '2016-06-13 15:48:45', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Our Story" font_container="tag:h1|text_align:left"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_video link="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ANm0pCw2nWk" css=".vc_custom_1490288632980{border-top-width: 5px !important;border-right-width: 5px !important;border-bottom-width: 5px !important;border-left-width: 5px !important;border-left-color: #ac8c43 !important;border-right-color: #ac8c43 !important;border-top-color: #ac8c43 !important;border-bottom-color: #ac8c43 !important;}"][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/2"][vc_column_text]Our philosophy has always been the same: to bring old world craftsmanship and care to the modern world of piano service.\r\n\r\nIn 2005, David and Kathy Hayes founded <i>Hayes Piano Restoration</i>. Their beginnings were humble, yet exciting.  Together as a newly married couple, David and Kathy wanted to start a piano servicing business that was dedicated to quality customer service and excellence.  Kathy scheduled appointments and ran the office from their dining room table while David performed service calls and piano restoration work.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]Right from the beginning, our customers recognized that something was unique and special about the way we conducted ourselves in the treatment of not only their pianos, but of them as well.\r\n\r\nAfter being blessed with significant growth, it became necessary to build a team of talented artisans who shared our vision for piano servicing and outstanding customer service; Artisan Piano Services was born.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignright wp-image-40" src="http://artisanpianos.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/IMG_7729.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 450px) 100vw, 450px" srcset="http://artisanpianos.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/IMG_7729.jpg 958w, http://artisanpianos.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/IMG_7729-300x134.jpg 300w" alt="IMG_7729" width="450" height="201" />Today, Artisan Piano Services has become one of the top piano servicing companies in the Pacific Northwest, with multiple locations and a strong desire to bring quality and craftsmanship to the piano industry.\r\n\r\n<em>“Time remembers those master artisans whose commitment to tradition and quality gave us a legacy of beauty, art and music.  Like piano builders of old, we take great pride in continuing this time-honored tradition of simplicity, elegance and integrity.  Our technicians are not only skilled piano tuners, but are also full-service rebuilders and consultants, doing whatever it takes to bring your piano back to its fullest life and potential.”</em>\r\n\r\n<em><strong>David Hayes, Founder. </strong></em>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'About Us', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about-us', '', '', '2017-03-24 00:04:36', '2017-03-23 17:04:36', '', 0, 'http://sw-themes.com/porto_dummy/?page_id=55', 0, 'page', '', 0),
