(517, 1, '2016-07-05 01:38:58', '2016-07-05 01:38:58', '[vc_row][vc_column][vc_custom_heading text="Piano Tuning" font_container="tag:h1|text_align:left" use_theme_fonts="yes"][vc_column_text]<strong>We are expert piano tuners</strong>\r\n\r\nTo experience the fullest possible sound and beauty of your piano, it must be properly tuned. We have built our business around this most important and basic element of piano maintenance and service.\r\n\r\nDepending on how often they are used, pianos generally need to be tuned 1-3 times each year to sound their best. Whether it has been a couple of months or 20 years since your piano was last tuned, give us a call to schedule an appointment with our expert piano tuners in both the Portland and Seattle/Bellevue areas.\r\n\r\n<strong>View our <a href="http://localhost/piano/full-service-packages">Piano Tuning &amp; Service Packages!</a></strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>What is included in your standard piano service?</strong>\r\n<h2><em>Tuning</em></h2>\r\nJust like your car, your piano is going to sound it’s best if it is regularly tuned. Because pianos are made mostly from wooden parts, the weather in the Pacific Northwest area has a significant impact on how quickly your piano goes out of tune. Regular tuning will provide more stability in the sound of your piano and increase its value. Our Portland and Seattle based piano tuners are an important investment in your prized instrument.\r\n<h2><em>Preliminary Cleaning</em></h2>\r\n<h2><em><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-404" src="http://artisanpianos.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2008-scion-back-300x156.png" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" srcset="http://artisanpianos.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2008-scion-back-300x156.png 300w, http://artisanpianos.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/04/2008-scion-back.png 708w" alt="2008-scion-back" data-id="404" /></em></h2>\r\nPianos are beautiful instruments but they collect a lot of dust and dirt over time. Properly cleaning your piano in part involves pulling on the strings, so it is important to have our piano tuners clean your piano at the same time your piano is tuned.\r\n<h2><em>Regulation of Pedals</em></h2>\r\nOur expert piano tuners will adjust your piano’s “action” – the inside mechanical parts of your piano, as well as your piano’s pedals. This is necessary to address the effects of use and changes in wood and wool that are caused by the weather in the Portland and Seattle areas. Regulating your piano’s action and pedals is a critical step in properly tuning your piano.\r\n<h2><em>Minor Repairs</em></h2>\r\nMany repairs can be made in your home during the piano tuning process.  Repairs that can be made with no additional service call (such as sticking keys or squeaky pedals) are included in our piano tuning service in both our locations in Portland and Seattle/Bellevue. Ask your technician for more details.\r\n<h2><em>Assessment of Your Piano’s Condition</em></h2>\r\nSometimes your piano needs more than just a minor repair. Our expert piano technicians can assess your piano’s condition from pedals to keys. We will provide you with important information and no-pressure estimates to make your Portland and Seattle area piano look and sound like new!\r\n<h2><em>Peace of Mind Guarantee</em></h2>\r\nWe guarantee that our expert piano technicians will leave you completely satisfied with your piano tuning service, or we will make it right.  Give us a call or <a href="http://localhost/piano/contact-us">contact us here</a> to learn more.\r\n\r\n<em>Our promise to you that if you ever have any problems after we service your piano, call us and we’ll send one of our technicians out free of charge to address your concerns. You have our word. </em><em>– Artisan Piano Services</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Let us know how we can best serve you!</em>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Piano Tuning', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'piano-tuning', '', '', '2017-03-28 11:01:46', '2017-03-28 04:01:46', '', 0, 'http://sw-themes.com/porto_dummy/?page_id=517', 0, 'page', '', 0),
